<subSubSection id="6D46C3FC92E4D3B4CDDC108A422F8C58" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="9A3E825990168933AF72990443105A37" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AFAB40FA8E71ED93B74BADCBAF3E80C7" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
In stark contrast to the splitting and naming of geographical populations of other 
<taxonomicName id="1D4DE37D42EC4825BD1BB381188876CB" authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="11D46B57FC0ECCF616AA87BF0C7AE2EC" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, 
<bibRefCitation id="B2C013C6D10A90FF4467DB9BAF559FCE" author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B20" refString="Leraut, P, 2012. Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids. NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">Leraut (2012</bibRefCitation>
: 98) lumps together a number of subspecific taxa of 
<taxonomicName id="8F711E1CBCDC0FB65EBC5D54CDC7AF02" baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1789" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhadamanthus">
<emphasis id="FA3FD2F0081B1C9A9D96A455E9DD8BF8" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena rhadamanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Esper, [1789]), all but one of which were considered valid by 
<bibRefCitation id="317A3E788D506DCE313D7F6C720D3C7A" author="Hofmann, A" journalOrPublisher="Harley Books, Colchester" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B17" refString="Hofmann, A, Tremewan, WG, 1996. A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae). Harley Books, Colchester" title="A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae)." year="1996">Hofmann and Tremewan (1996</bibRefCitation>
: 130-131). The latter authors accept that less variation is exhibited in the populations occurring in France (east of the Pyrenees) compared to those in the Iberian Peninsula where they exhibit a mosaic of extreme geographical variation, with phenotypes ranging from 
<normalizedToken id="AC02FAE679EC0D54407A5482A74A7E1D" originalValue="‘normal’">'normal'</normalizedToken>
and melanistic to individuals with the forewing ground colour powdered with white scales (griseoid) and reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName id="D46B49ECD3076ED09830E2F5EC9ACE8D" authorityName="Oberthuer" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. grisea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="grisea">
<emphasis id="B945CAD8A9BCEB2D8E5389141606506D" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena rhadamanthus grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The subspecific nominal taxa relevant to their treatment by 
<bibRefCitation id="AB7F869857124166D47328FFD39D1857" author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B20" refString="Leraut, P, 2012. Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids. NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">Leraut (2012</bibRefCitation>
: 98) are discussed in detail below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
